' Relationships
IGraphicsDevice <|.. WebGPUDevice
IRenderer <|.. Renderer
ICommandRecorder <|.. CommandRecorder
CommandRecorder --> RecorderState : owns
CommandRecorder --> IGraphicsDevice : uses
Renderer --> IGraphicsDevice : owns
Renderer --> SwapChain : manages
Renderer --> FrameManager : uses
Renderer --> CommandPool : uses
Renderer --> ICommandRecorder : creates
SwapChain --> IGraphicsDevice : uses
ICommandRecorder --> RenderTarget : renders to
ICommandRecorder --> Pipeline : uses
ICommandRecorder --> BindGroup : binds
FrameManager --> FrameData : manages
CommandPool --> ICommandRecorder : pools
SwapChain --> RenderTarget : provides
Application --> IRenderer : uses
Application --> Scene : owns

note right of IGraphicsDevice
    **Backend Abstraction:**
    - All WebGPU API calls encapsulated here
    - No direct WebGPU usage outside this class
    - Future backends: Vulkan, Metal, D3D12
end note

note right of CommandRecorder
    **Key Design Decisions:**
    - Explicit BeginRenderPass/EndRenderPass
    - nullptr = current backbuffer
    - No automatic pass closing
    - State validation in debug mode
end note

note right of Renderer
    **Frame Flow:**
    1. BeginFrame() - Acquire backbuffer
    2. Record commands
    3. EndFrame() - Submit & Present
    Triple buffering for smooth rendering
end note

@enduml